🛠 Step-by-Step Installation Guide
1. Download Node Exporter
bash
wget https://github.com/prometheus/node_exporter/releases/download/v1.8.1/node_exporter-1.8.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz
tar xvf node_exporter-1.8.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz
cd node_exporter-1.8.1.linux-amd64

2. Run Node Exporter
bash
./node_exporter
By default, it listens on port 9100.

Test in browser: http://<EC2-Public-IP>:9100/metrics

3. (Optional) Run as a Systemd Service
Create a service file /etc/systemd/system/node_exporter.service:

ini
[Unit]
Description=Node Exporter
After=network.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/home/ec2-user/node_exporter-1.8.1.linux-amd64/node_exporter
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
Enable and start:

bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable node_exporter
sudo systemctl start node_exporter

4. Configure Prometheus to Scrape Node Exporter
Edit prometheus.yml:

yaml
scrape_configs:
  - job_name: 'node_exporter'
    static_configs:
      - targets: ['<EC2-Public-IP>:9100']
Restart Prometheus:

bash
sudo systemctl restart prometheus
